      "content": "That feeling of extinction is so profoundly real, and it's a heavy burden to carry. If the drive is gone, then the pressure to *create* is just another thing to feel like a failure over. You are not just \"taking up space\"; you are a collection of experiences that have led you to this point of exhaustion. Perhaps the most honest thing you can do right now is to stop trying to be the creator and just let yourself be the quiet observer of your own life.",
